title: WasteServ receives S.A.F.E Award for 'commitment to employee wellbeing'
description: WasteServ has been recognised by the Foundation for Social Welfare Services (FSWS) with the S.A.F.E Award for its efforts to promote healthier and safer workplaces, the entity said Saturday. This award highlights the company's strong commitment to employee wellbeing through the implementation of various initiatives."Employee wellbeing is of utmost importance for WasteServ. As a workplace, we are determined to help and support any employees suffering from substance use disorders so that they can recover. It is essential for us to provide a supportive, stigma‐free, and recovery‐friendly environment," stated WasteServ CEO Richard Bilocca.The S.A.F.E programme focuses on preventing addiction in the workplace and providing support to employees who may be facing substance‐related challenges. WasteServ's participation reflects its dedication to creating a safe, supportive, and recovery‐oriented work environment.Over the past years, WasteServ has made significant investments in initiatives aimed at supporting its workforce. Alongside the introduction of family‐friendly measures and flexible working hours, the company has established a dedicated Recovery Support Unit (RSU). This specialised unit offers one‐to‐one guidance and services delivered by an experienced multidisciplinary team of professionals, ensuring that employees dealing with substance use disorders have access to personalised care and the best possible support on their recovery journey.Receiving the S.A.F.E Award further strengthens WasteServ's ongoing commitment to building a healthier and more inclusive workplace for all, the company said.
